  "12.5°C — the temperature is split between twice the volume": "",
  "Temperature is intensive. When you combine two samples at the same temperature, the result is that same temperature — not the sum. The volume and mass (extensive) will double to 200 mL, but the temperature stays at 25°C.": "",
  "A geologist finds an unknown mineral and records: mass = 45 g, volume = 15 cm³, color = silver-gray, hardness = 6 on Mohs scale. Which measurements are most useful for identifying the mineral?": "",
