  "Only mass — it is the most reliable measurement": "",
  "Color, hardness, and density (45 g ÷ 15 cm³ = 3.0 g/cm³) are all intensive properties unique to a substance. These can be compared to known mineral reference values for identification. Mass and volume alone (extensive) would vary with sample size.": "",
